parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unpredictable ABS activation can lead to a sudden loss of braking power, increasing the stopping distance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: ABS activates unnecessarily when driving over bumps
causing a sudden loss of braking power
the brake pedal drops to the floor
and the vehicle takes a longer distance to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sudden loss of braking power can lead to accidents, especially when driving at moderate to high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal drops to the floor
and the vehicle takes a longer distance to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Line Leaks in Cold Weather
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel line leaks can cause raw gasoline fumes to enter the passenger compartment, creating a serious safety hazard of fire or explosion.
symptoms: Strong raw gasoline smell in the passenger compartment
especially during cold weather startup; fuel smell becomes stronger when the vehicle is stopped; fuel leaks onto the engine
causing smoke to rise from under the hood; fuel smell is overpowering and can cause headaches and dizziness.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Line Leaks and Engine Fire Risk
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks can cause engine fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor inside the vehicle
fuel smell in the engine compartment
fuel leaking onto the engine block
